The paper deals with the problem of mining frequent itemsets from massive datasets, which is a core problem in data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of different data structures to enhance the efficiency and scalability of the Apriori algorithm, which falls under the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of MapReduce, which is a popular technology for processing big datasets, and therefore falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on both real-life and synthetic datasets, which is a common practice in the sub-category cs.DM (Data Mining).
